{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-17T03:43:08.917Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1776397388917_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-022@20260416t181925z-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-022@20260416T181925Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-17\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** \n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/silence_budget.py`\n- `tests/test_silence_budget_rule.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/__init__.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/daemon.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py`\n- `tests/test_first_boot.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe `SilenceBudgetRule` (R10) correctly implements the per-voice accumulator math using the formula `rest_budget += (target_density - actual_density) * dt * k`. Enforcement at phrase boundaries accurately triggers either a breath extension (if an R6 breath is present) or a tacet-drop for the subsequent phrase when the budget exceeds the threshold.\n\n## Completeness\nThe implementation is complete according to the spec. The rule handles:\n- Accumulator math and budget tracking across multiple phrases.\n- Breath extension path (R6 search and length doubling).\n- Tacet-drop path (velocity zeroing and metadata marking).\n- Budget reset after triggering.\n- Role-gating (eligible roles only).\n- Scaling via `k` parameter.\n\nThe test suite (17 new tests) provides exhaustive coverage for all these scenarios, including edge cases like single phrases or `k=0`.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows established SenseWeave render rule patterns, including the use of frozen dataclasses, the `applies_to`/`apply` protocol, and the `role_is_eligible` filter. Integration into `render/rules/__init__.py` is correct.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities were introduced. The implementation is a pure-function transformation of tracker data.\n\n## Quality\nCode quality is high, with clear separation of concerns in helper functions and comprehensive unit tests. The full repository test suite (2895 tests) passes, ensuring no regressions.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [x] Minor: `pip install -e '.[dev]'` failed with `OSError: [Errno 1] Operation not permitted` on `/Users/anthony/.local/lib` due to macOS Seatbelt restrictions. This did not impact verification as all dependencies were already present and the test suite ran successfully.\n\n## Hardening Verification\n- **`bootstrap_identity()` Startup Path:** Confirmed that `bootstrap_identity()` is invoked before `FirstBootAnnouncer` in both `my-claw/tools/daemon.py` (line 2462) and `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` (line 3542).\n- **Identity Persistence:** `tests/test_first_boot.py` (TestStartupIdentityPersistence) verifies that identity is minted on first boot and persists across subsequent reboots.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation of the Silence Budget rule is robust and the test coverage is excellent. No further changes are required.\n"}}
